# FANUC KAREL Conventions

Apply when authoring or reviewing `.KL` (KAREL source) and `.PC` (compiled) programs.

## Program structure

```
PROGRAM <program_name>
%ALPHABETIZE
%COMMENT = '<short description>'
%NOLOCKGROUP
%STACKSIZE = 2000

VAR
    <declarations>

ROUTINE <name>(...)
    ...
END <name>

BEGIN
    ...
END <program_name>
```

Program name uppercase, <=36 chars, no leading digit.

## Directives

- `%ALPHABETIZE` - keep symbol lists sorted.
- `%COMMENT = '...'` - short, shown on pendant.
- `%NOLOCKGROUP` - required when the program must run without owning motion groups (common for socket / background KAREL).
- `%STACKSIZE` - set explicitly; default is usually too small for any non-trivial program.
- `%ENVIRONMENT SYSTEM, MEMO, PATHOP, IOSETUP` (and friends) - include only the environments you need; unnecessary envs bloat the binary.

## Variables

- Globals in `VAR` section at top, one per line, named with purpose and type suffix:
  - `n_style  : INTEGER`
  - `pr_pick  : XYZWPR`
  - `status   : INTEGER`
- Avoid single-letter names outside loop indices.
- Use `CONST` for magic numbers.

## Routines

- `ROUTINE` names verb-first: `get_style`, `open_socket`, `compute_approach`.
- Return via `RETURN(value)` at the end of a function, never mid-branch.
- Parameters by name and type; no positional tricks.

## Error handling

- Use `CONDITION` and `HANDLER` blocks for async faults.
- Synchronous errors: check `status` after every system call that can fail (`SET_VAR`, `GET_VAR`, socket calls, file I/O).
- Abort gracefully: close sockets, files, pipes. Never leave a socket in `SERVER_START` without a matching `SERVER_STOP`.

## Socket messaging (Ricochet / PC SDK interop)

- Use `MSG_CONNECT` + `MSG_DISCO` pairs. Every open has a close.
- Read into fixed-size buffers; bounds-check before parsing.
- Idle timeout is mandatory; reconnect policy must be documented.
- Protocol framed with length prefix or newline delimiter. Never "just read" and assume the whole message arrived.

## Motion control KAREL

- If the program owns motion (not `%NOLOCKGROUP`), follow all the TP motion hygiene rules.
- Use `MOVE_AXS`, `MOVE_TO` with explicit termination and speed.
- Do not mix KAREL motion with concurrent TP motion on the same group unless the design is explicitly multi-group coordinated.

## Stream Motion

- Stream Motion (`SM`) programs have strict cycle timing (typically 8 ms). Every cycle must produce a command or skip cleanly.
- Degraded-mode behavior (sensor failure, network loss, data stale) must be specified up front, not left implicit.

## Anti-patterns

- Unbounded reads from sockets.
- `ABORT` or `FORCE STOP` without prior cleanup.
- Modifying system variables without a written justification (`$MCR`, `$MOR`, `$SCR`, etc.).
- KAREL programs that silently swallow errors (`status := 0` after an error).
- Shared globals modified from multiple KAREL programs without mutex.

